\v 1 He that takes vengeance will find vengeance from the Lord;
\q1 And he will surely make firm his sins.
\q1
\v 2 Forgive your neighbor the hurt that he has done \add you; \add*
\q1 And then your sins will be pardoned when you pray.
\q1
\v 3 Man cherishes anger against man;
\q1 And does he seek healing from the Lord?
\q1
\v 4 Upon a man like himself he has no mercy;
\q1 And does he make supplication for his own sins?
\q1
\v 5 He being himself flesh nourishes wrath:
\q1 Who will make atonement for his sins?
\q1
\v 6 Remember your last end, and cease from enmity:
\q1 \add Remember \add* corruption and death, and remain in the commandments.
\q1
\v 7 Remember the commandments, and be not angry with your neighbor;
\q1 And \add remember \add* the covenant of the Highest, and wink at ignorance.
