\v 10 \f + \fr 28:10 \ft The order of the lines in this verse is uncertain. \f* As is the fuel of the fire, so will it burn;
\q1 And as the stoutness of the strife is, \add so \add* will it burn:
\q1 As is the strength of the man, \add so \add* will be his wrath;
\q1 And as is his wealth, \add so \add* he will exalt his anger.
\q1
\v 11 A contention begun in haste kindles a fire;
\q1 And a hasty fighting sheds blood.
\q1
\v 12 If you blow a spark, it will burn;
\q1 And if you spit upon it, it will be quenched:
\q1 And both these shall come out of your mouth.
