\q1
\v 13 Curse the whisperer and double-tongued:
\q1 For he has destroyed many that were at peace.
\q1
\v 14 A third person’s tongue has shaken many,
\q1 And dispersed them from nation to nation;
\q1 And it has pulled down strong cities,
\q1 And overthrown the houses of great men.
\q1
\v 15 A third person’s tongue has cast out brave women,
\q1 And deprived them of their labors.
\q1
\v 16 He that listens to it will not find rest,
\q1 Nor shall he dwell quietly.
\q1
\v 17 The stroke of a whip makes a mark in the flesh;
\q1 But the stroke of a tongue will break bones.
\q1
\v 18 Many have fallen by the edge of the sword:
\q1 Yet not so many as those who have fallen because of the tongue.
\q1
\v 19 Happy is he that is sheltered from it,
\q1 That has not passed through the wrath thereof;
\q1 That has not drawn its yoke,
\q1 And has not been bound with its bands.
\q1
\v 20 For the yoke thereof is a yoke of iron,
\q1 And the bands thereof are bands of brass.
\q1
\v 21 The death thereof is an evil death;
\q1 And Hades were better than it.
\q1
\v 22 It shall not have rule over godly men;
\q1 And they shall not be burned in its flame.
\q1
\v 23 They that forsake the Lord shall fall into it;
\q1 And it shall burn among them, and shall not be quenched:
\q1 It shall be sent forth upon them as a lion;
\q1 And as a leopard it shall destroy them.
\q1
\v 24 Look that you hedge your possession about with thorns;
\q1 Bind up your silver and your gold;
\q1
\v 25 And make a balance and a weight for your words;
\q1 And make a door and a bar for your mouth.
\q1
\v 26 Take heed lest you slip therein;
\q1 Lest you fall before one that lies in wait.
